Steps to reproduce:
Use "Convert switch statement to expression" feature on this code:

```
private static int SwitchMethod(TestEnum testEnum)
    {
        switch (testEnum)
        {
            case TestEnum.Option1:
                return 1;

            case TestEnum.Option2:
            case TestEnum.Option3:
                return 2;
            default:
                return 0;
        }
    }
```
Incorrectly generated code: TestEnum.Option2**or**TestEnum.Option3 => 2,

```
private static int SwitchMethod(TestEnum testEnum)
    {
        return testEnum switch
        {
            TestEnum.Option1 => 1,
            TestEnum.Option2orTestEnum.Option3 => 2, //<--- !!!! incorrectly concatenated 'OR' operator
            _ => 0,
        };
    }
```
Expected: TestEnum.Option2 **or** TestEnum.Option3 => 2,

```
private static int SwitchMethod(TestEnum testEnum)
    {
        return testEnum switch
        {
            TestEnum.Option1 => 1,
            TestEnum.Option2 or TestEnum.Option3 => 2, // <-- notice spaces between
            _ => 0,
        };
    }
```

